    ## `blur` Plugin
    This plugin can only be used as an extension to the `360` plugin. It renders additional frame images and fades them out over time
    which simulates a motion blur effect

  +example
    #spritespin-example
    script(type='text/javascript' src='/release/spritespin.js')
    script(type='text/javascript').
      SpriteSpin.create({
        target: '#spritespin-example',
        source: SpriteSpin.source('http://spritespin.ginie.eu/images/rad_zoom_{frame}.jpg', {
          frame: [1,34], digits: 3
        }),
        sense: -1,
        plugins: [
          'drag', // changes frame on drag
          '360',  // display array or sprite of images
          'blur'  // adds and fades additional frames to somulate blur
        ]
      })

  :markdown-it
    ### Options

    The blur effect can be controlled with the following options
    - `fadeTime`
    - `frameTime`
    - `cssBlur`

  +example
    #spritespin-example-2
    script(type='text/javascript').
      SpriteSpin.create({
        target: '#spritespin-example-2',
        source: SpriteSpin.source('http://spritespin.ginie.eu/images/rad_zoom_{frame}.jpg', {
          frame: [1,34], digits: 3
        }),
        sense: -1,
        animate: false,
        plugins: [
          'drag', // changes frame on drag
          '360',  // display array or sprite of images
          {
            name: 'blur',
            options: {
              fadeTime: 200,
              frameTime: 16,
              cssBlur: true
            }
          }
        ]
      })

